title: Joint Targeting Officer
description: Serves as the Joint Targeting Officer for the Combined Joint Fires Element (CJFE). Primarily responsible for synchronizing, de-conflicting and coordinating combined and joint fires planning for the Combined Forces Commander (CFC); determines, authors and disseminates guidance for targeting priorities, target nomination, and theater fire support processes. Manages 25,000 targets on the Joint Target List (JTL), Restricted Target List (RTL), and No Strike List (NSL) for the entire theater of Korea. Synchronizes and integrates efforts across numerous staff working groups in support of theater lethal and non-lethal fires. Synchronizes cyber targeting effects with maneuver unit operations in support of the CFC Commanders operational plan. Action Officer responsible for managing the Joint Targeting Coordination Board (JTCB), Targeting Effects Working Group (TEWG) and the Targeting Special Effects Working Group (TSEWG); events which drive targeting efforts supporting war fighting operations for 30,000 U.S. Soldiers and 600,000 Republic of Korea Soldiers throughout the Greater Seoul Metropolitan Area (GSMA). Advises and mentors Korean field grade officers of the Ground Component Command (GCC) targeting cell on target nomination; Billing Official for responsible for $36000 budget.

title: Senior Cyber Security Manager
description: Responsible for the characterization and mitigation of threats to Department of Defense computer networks worldwide. Develops operating procedures and battle rhythm for a workforce of 61 multi-service and civilian cyber analysts and staff. Provides quality assurance for SIGINT reports released to the intelligence enterprise and mitigation strategies employed within the Global information Grid (GIG); conducts defensive cyber operations (DCO) within one of 6 national level cyber centers. Coordinates and facilitates the development of time-sensitive cyber security countermeasures designed to defeat cyber threats to the GIG; conducts and manages computer network defense (CND), computer network exploitation (CNE), and Cyber ISR operations. Responsible for maintaining the common operating picture of adversary cyber space and operations which is used to direct national joint cyber community operations.

title: Executive Officer
description: Supervised logistical and administrative support for a Multi-Discipline Company which provides Counterintelligence support for Combined Joint Task Force- 101. title: SGX Coach
description: Serves as the only certified coach for Spartan Group Exercise (SGX) located in Hawaii. SGX is designed to create an exhilarating, community driven, group atmosphere of fitness, nutrition, and performance that optimizes individual performance in Spartan Races, as well as health and vitality throughout daily life. SGX is about changing the mind and body from the inside out. SGX prepares people for life! It is not about curling, running or biking, it is about pushing, pulling, jumping, stretching, breathing and sweating. Key Achievements: ➢ Mar 2014 - Lead the Aloha Stadium Hurricane Heat in 2014 which included nearly 40 participants. ➢ Feb 2014 - Lead the Honolulu Boys and Girls Club fitness initiative which included over 100 children ranging in ages from 6-14 years old. ➢ Jan 2014 - Lead Hawaii's first Aloha Stadium Spartan "300 WOD" which consisted of nearly 300 participants. ➢ 2013-Present - Leads dozens of workouts throughout the island of Oahu. ➢ May 2013 - Lead the Spartan Race fitness initiative for over 200 children during Hawaii's ESPN1440 children's fitness expo.

title: Senior Career Counselor
description: Conducts retention and reenlistment interviews in a Combat Environment. Travels great distances via convoy or air to counsel soldiers on their Army options, incentives, and benefits. Determines soldier's eligibility to immediately reenlist or extend; reviews reenlistment and extension documents for accuracy; coordinates retention ceremonies. Advises commanders on criteria for selection of unit level retention NCOs. Advises soldiers on declination of continued serv ice statements. Conducts inspections of and trains unit level retention NCOs. Briefs leaders on matters relating to retention activities. Maintains liaison with local personnel and finance offices. Chief Senior Advisor to the commander at Brigade (5k or more) or comparable sized units on all areas of the retention program. Key Achievements: ➢ 2011 - Attained Lean Six Sigma Green Belt Certification Advises commanders on all areas of the retention program. Reviews retention actions for accuracy. Interprets regulations and provides guidance for subordinates, Assists in the development and direction of command retention programs. Conducts conferences and seminars for retention agendas. Assists leaders and strength management personnel in implementation and operation of the strength management program. Conducts staff assistance visits. Plans and conducts retention training; evaluates subordinates' training presentations and interviews, provide feedback. Manages objectives, statistics and awards program. Explains unit performance data to leaders and superiors. Evaluates subordinate's conduct of a retention interview. Determines soldiers' eligibility for retention duty. Plans and conducts retention training for Soldiers and Leaders.

title: Career Counselor
description: Conducts retention and reenlistment interviews in a Combat Environment. Travels great distances via convoy or air to counsel soldiers on their Army options, incentives, and benefits. Determines soldier's eligibility to immediately reenlist or extend; reviews reenlistment and extension documents for accuracy; coordinates retention ceremonies. Advises commanders on criteria for selection of unit level retention NCOs. Advises soldiers on declination of continued serv ice statements. Conducts inspections of and trains unit level retention NCOs. Briefs leaders on matters relating to retention activities. Maintains liaison with local personnel and finance offices. Chief Senior Advisor to the commander at Battalion (1,700 Soldiers) and Brigade (3,800 Soldiers) or comparable sized units on all areas of the retention program. Advises commanders on all areas of the retention program. Reviews retention actions for accuracy. Interprets regulations and provides guidance for subordinates, Assists in the development and direction of command retention programs. Conducts conferences and seminars for retention agendas. Assists leaders and strength management personnel in implementation and operation of the strength management program. Conducts staff assistance visits. Plans and conducts retention training; evaluates subordinates' training presentations and interviews, provide feedback. Manages objectives, statistics and awards program. Explains unit performance data to leaders and superiors. Evaluates subordinate's conduct of a retention interview. Determines soldiers' eligibility for retention duty. Plans and conducts retention training for Soldiers and Leaders. Key Achievements: ➢ May 2007 - Graduated Advance Noncommisioned Officer Course (ANCOC) as the Distinguished Honor Graduate. ➢ May 2007 - Selected as the Advance Noncommisioned Officer Course (ANCOC) Distinguished Leadership Awardee. ➢ Awardee of the Adjutant General's Benjamin Harrison Medal.

summary: Highly adaptable and disciplined professional with experience in the intelligence community and adapt to working in changing environments, seeks to contribute interpersonal skills in a team and project-oriented environment. -TOP-SECRET/Sensitive Compartment Information (SCI) clearance with a Counter Intelligence (CI) poly -Work collaboratively and effectively in a fast paced and multicultural environment -Ability and willingness to perform a wide variety of task, change focus to meet specified deliverables and customers need. -Experience working in a compartmented 24-hour operation facility -Usage of Analytical Skills/tools include: Microsoft Office, Octave, ArcView, Skywriter, Analyst Notebook, Ravenwing, Oilstock, Sentinal, Centerpoint, Salem, SIGINT Navigator, WVT, DVT, Goodwrench, Pursuit Central, M2Extra, JMSEL, COLISEUM, TAC, JTIMS, PSView, PSL, Xkeyscore, Intelink, Google Earth, Hot-r, Vintage Harvest, M3 -Significant knowledge of Intelligence Community (IC) elements, functions, requirements and interrelationships among the IC element -Knowledgeable of various Information Technology Application-UNIX, LINUX, Windows 98/00/XP/VISTA and SUN, SYBASE -Knowledge of network topologies -Capable of creating intelligence reports or assessments based on the analysis of SIGINT and non-SIGINT material.

title: All-Source Intelligence Analyst
description: As an All-Source Intel Analyst, I am responsible for analyzing current intelligence holdings to identify gaps, and subsequent intelligence collection requirements. Provide key analysis on countries of interest. Draft and edit intelligence reports, plans and briefings within reporting and dissemination guidelines. Research unclassified and classified databases for use in written products. While reporting we must follow USSID doctrine, especially focusing on USSID 18. Provide analyst support to a Tier 1 exercise supporting US EUCOM command staff and training audience of 40,000 people. Provide research support for analysts who produce Intelligence Community reports and briefings. Daily support field efforts to target, assess, and recruit foreign intelligence assets. I provide guidance, case management, and support to field collection operations. Review and evaluate the overall reporting from assets to help determine asset validity. Research and coordinate threat assessments to support the Commander and/or leaders in the U.S. civilian intelligence community. Senior scripter replicating COCOM responses to dynamic adversary operation using COLISEUM and JMSEL databases. Conduct Briefings and training on varies military functions and guidelines.

title: Senior Records Management Liaison
description: Establish and implement a records management program for a federal agency. Handle classified and unclassified documents on a daily basis. Give recommendations to the government's POC for decision that was suitable for their need. In addition, drafting and implementing accurate, thorough, and up-to-date records management policies and procedures to facilitate effective and efficient record-keeping programs using SharePoint. Arrange, index, store and classify records. In this capacity analyzing extremely complex problems and report recommendations to the government's POC for decision that was suitable for their need. Ensure the implementation of retention and disposal schedules of records, Vital Records, FOIA and Privacy Act and related topics. Review completed FOIA request for appropriate material to be or not be released, composing response letters, and clarifying requests. Coordinate with program offices on conducting searches for responsive documents; and negotiating with submitters of records, and with requestors of those records, to clarify requests in order to make release determinations or recommendations. Provide training to all variety of Divisions, branches and teams, in support of the war fighter within the federal agency. Perform newcomers brief to all agency personnel to demonstrate proper use of the server and how files are filed in the file structure, rules and regulations of record and non-record information. Serves as a liaison and primary contact with the records staff at the Washington Headquarters Service and NARA. Supervise the retirement, transfer and/or pre-accessioning of electronic and hard copy records for each division. Conduct daily desk side and classroom setting training on various government sites. Update training material as needed to meet the government client standards.

title: SIGNAL ANALYST & DATA COLLECTION ANALYST
description: Mission Support Hub Operated signal intelligence (SIGINT) equipment and prepared logs and technical reports and brief them to the commanding officers. Performed processing and analysis of time sensitive data and authored technical reports. Searched the radio frequency spectrum to collect, identify and record target communications or foreign instrumentation signals. Performed analysis to determine signal parameter for identification and processing. Stored files in databases for future achievements, exploitation and reference. Processes, edits and scans raw material before releasing electrical transmissions to sensitive external customers. Maintained the integrity of communication link, utilizing extensive troubleshooting techniques during periods of outage, in other necessary situations. Performed traffic analysis to ensure compliancy with data exchange agreement. Updates and maintains archives and working database tables to research, exploit and track specific target behavior. Provided error corrections to raw material on a timely basis. Coordinates collection management with the appropriate organizations, ensuring operational tasking is accurate and obtainable based on system capabilities. Performed daily task and operations on High Frequency and Overhead systems. Conducted training and prepared briefs for Sergeant time training. Monitored Xkeyscore by conducting daily checks to ensure that they database was running for the use of other offices. Periodically conducted check balances to ensure the system was not being misused. I have a understanding of Xkeyscore's function and use.

Constantly conferred with other analysts and teammates to ensure open lines of communication and maintain consistency throughout the team.

title: Intelligence Analyst
description: Intelligence Analyst involved in all aspects of the Harmony Document Exploitation (DOCEX) process. "Translated" technical instructions to create user guides understandable to non-technical personnel. Wrote and published meeting minutes, ensured parties completed assigned tasks.

title: Language Program Manager @ 94th Intelligence Squadron
description: Revamped unit's language program during change from 50 linguists in three languages to 150+ linguists in 45+ languages. Provided future language requirements and training recommendations to decision makers. Responsible for all aspects of language training (acquisition, maintenance, improvement, proficiency testing), reference materials acquisition, language training scheduling and travel. Participated in service- and national-level conferences and planning meetings. Orchestrated collaboration projects with National Security Agency, Defense Intelligence Agency, Defense Attaché Service. Ensured personnel developed and improved language, cultural, target-specific, analytic interpretation, technology expertise, adaptability, and customer relations skills. Co-authored detailed training plans including training timeline, forms for documentation of training, skills evaluations upon completion of training. Wrote and published meeting minutes, ensured parties completed assigned tasks. Prepared and edited personnel performance appraisals as direct and second-tier supervisor. Prepared program and personnel award nomination packages.

title: Various units and locations
description: Language collection operations and training; intelligence analysis; preparing/releasing KLIEGLIGHT, EGRAM, CRITIC, and other reports; machine-assisted (MT) and manual translation of technical and other materials; PROFORMA signals analysis; prototype equipment testing; creation of technical materials and working aids; database maintenance; technical and reference materials librarian; supervisor of multi-service library facility; public affairs program. Consolidated four technical libraries into one joint account holding more than 3,000 physical documents; posted changes & deletions; implemented new and removed superseded documents. Co-authored detailed training plans including training timeline, forms for documentation of training, skills evaluations upon completion of training. Wrote and published meeting minutes, ensured parties completed assigned tasks. Re-formatted more than 25 technical reports prepared by multiple authors using different word processing programs and incorporated into a specialized handbook to ensure textual and schematic uniformity and professional presentation. Analyzed data, prepared and edited reports to meet real-time and long-term intelligence needs and develop future program requirements. Prepared and edited personnel performance appraisals as direct and second-tier supervisor. Prepared program and personnel award nomination packages.

description: 2012 NSA Washington Operational Performer of the Year 2012 NSOC Military Performer of the Year, Senior Enlisted 2012 S2J Weapons & Space Military Performer of the Year, Senior Enlisted 2012 NSOC Military Performer of the Quarter for the 4th Quarter, Senior Enlisted 2012 S2J Military Performer of the Quarter for 3rd Quarter, Senior Enlisted 2014 NSOC Military Performer of the Quarter for the 1st Quarter, Senior Enlisted National Security Operations Center (NSOC) focal point relating to Technical SIGINT disciplines (ELINT, FISINT, PROFORMA, OPIR); provides timely mapping, graphics, and analysis to leadership of threats & scenarios about deployed weapon systems and in development Liaison with Defense Special Missile and Aerospace Center (DEFSMAC); alerting NSOC on missile and space events; performs near-real-time analysis of events using multi-discipline methods Composes executive level briefings on global and evolving events relating to foreign weapons and space systems, deployed weapons systems, in research and development (R&D) Collaborates with developers to NSOC Common Operating Picture (COP); maintains total situational awareness of world events, operations of U.S., Allied and coalition forces; remains cognizant of global situations; provides cryptologic support to U.S. Military Commands and IC Uses multi-source SIGINT data and feeds to monitor maritime proliferation of weapons; creates graphical slides and written input to wrap-ups on significant air and air defense events; answers COCOM time-sensitive requests for information (RFI); recognizes ELINT parameters of radar and correlates to function, all supporting strategic, tactical, and operational plans and products Instrumental in U.S. Air Force F-16 aircraft Personal Recovery (PR) event. Through utilization of streaming data on Common Operating Picture (COP) and coordination. Pilot rescued

summary: • 19+ years U.S. Air Force experience serving SIGINT Tasking, Collection, Processing Exploitation Dissemination (PED) requirements enabling tactical, operational, and strategic missions • 16 years experience as an Analytic Subject Matter Expert for SIGINT-derived products and services for National, DoD, and Intelligence Communities (IC) • 11 years as a SIGINT Operator and Technician providing threat warning and force protection for Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance (ISR) missions • 3 years as Distributed Common Ground System (DCGS) operator and Program Manager • 3 years as Technical SIGINT Coordinator (TSSC) in NSOC relating to Weapons and Space • 5 years as Information Operations (IO) Technician, integrated EW, C4I, and OPSEC into Air and Space Operations Center (AOC) planning, execution and assessments • Electronic Warfare Coordination Cell (EWCC) Duty Officer deployed in support of combat operations in Iraq and Afghanistan providing force protection over U.S. ground troops • Facilitated NSA's analysis mission in its combat support function to exercises of the military, NATO, and the U.S. Cryptologic System; ULCHI FOCUS LENS (UFL), AUSTERE CHALLENGE • Seasoned professional with exceptional complex problem solving skills and extensive corporate knowledge of intelligence processes with strong record of managerial and technical achievement • Proven interpersonal communicator and extensive experience in preparing written technical products, developing graphic presentations, and briefings to any level or any size group • Provided assessments of foreign / adversary country Order of Battles (OBs) • Team builder and change agent who readily accepts difficult challenges and insists on excellence • Leadership and management in support of worldwide military and cryptologic operations • Expert user of various Intelligence Community (IC) Tools and Databases, MS Outlook Word Power Point Excel
